“collective
investment scheme” means any pooled investment scheme, fund or
vehicle irrespective of legal form;

“company” means any body corporate
or any entity that is treated as a body corporate for tax
purposes;

in the case of the Turks and Caicos Islands, the
Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Finance or a person or authority
designated by him in writing;

“Contracting Party” means the
Netherlands or the Turks and Caicos Islands as the context
requires;

“criminal tax matters” means tax
matters involving intentional conduct which is liable to prosecution
under the criminal laws of the requesting Party;

“person”
means an individual (“natural person”), a company, or any
other body or group of persons;

the
identity of the person under examination or
investigation;

to the extent known, the name and address of any
person believed to be in possession or control of the information
requested;

The receiving authority
shall on request inform the supplying authority about the use of the
supplied data and the results achieved thereby;

The supplying and the receiving authority shall be
obliged to keep official records of the supply and receipt of personal
data;

the
other Contracting Party does not engage in effective exchange of
information;

the Turks and Caicos Islands enter into an
agreement with another jurisdiction which provides for other forms of
exchange of information;

